title: Wind Solar Wind Experiment, 92-sec Solar Wind Alpha and Proton Anisotropy Analysis - K. Ogilvie (NASA GSFC)

info.x_cadence_note: Counts based on variable 'Epoch' in https://cdaweb.gsfc.nasa.gov/sp_phys/data/wind/swe/swe_h1/1994/wi_h1_swe_19941117_v01.cdf. The most common cadence occurred for 73.5450% of the 139 timesteps. Cadence = 74642 [ms] = PT1M14.642S.
